{"id":381,"date":"2011-01-16T01:22:17","date_gmt":"2011-01-16T05:22:17","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=381"},"modified":"2025-03-03T15:53:48","modified_gmt":"2025-03-03T11:53:48","slug":"allah-is-kind-loves-kindness","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/01\/16\/allah-is-kind-loves-kindness\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Rifq: Allah loves gentleness, even with wrongdoers"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Aisha reported: A group of Jews asked permission to visit the Prophet and when they were admitted, they said, &#8220;Death be upon you!&#8221; I said to them, &#8220;Rather, death and the curse of Allah be upon you!&#8221; The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, &#8220;<strong>O Aisha, Allah is gentle and He loves gentleness in all matters.<\/strong>&#8221; I said, &#8220;Have you not heard what they said?&#8221; The Prophet said, &#8220;<strong>I said to them: And upon you.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6927, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2165<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Muttafaqun\u00a0<\/strong><\/em><em><strong>Alayhi<\/strong> <\/em>(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0627\u0633\u0652\u062a\u064e\u0623\u0652\u0630\u064e\u0646\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0647\u0652\u0637\u064c \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u064a\u064e\u0647\u064f\u0648\u062f\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064f\u0648\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u064e\u0651\u0627\u0645\u0